vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
direction: down
title: |'md
  ## Padding Algorithm Decision Tree: One Block vs Two Blocks
  **FIPS 180-4 §5.1.1** — `total_padded = ⌈(used + 8) / 64⌉ × 64`
'| {near: top-center}
input: |'md
  **INPUT**
  `msg[0..len-1]`
  `len` bytes
'| {
  style: {
    fill: "#C084FC"
    font-color: "#1E003C"
    border-radius: 8
    bold: true
  }
}
compute_used: |'md
  **STEP 1: Append marker byte**
  `used = len + 1`
  Write `0x80` at `data[len]`
  _(remaining bytes zeroed by memset)_
'| {
  style: {
    fill: "#93C5FD"
    font-color: "#00194A"
    border-radius: 8
  }
}
branch: |'md
  **STEP 2: Can length field fit?**
  Is `used ≤ 56`?
  _(i.e., ≥ 8 bytes remain in current 64-byte block)_
'| {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#FDE68A"
    font-color: "#2D1B00"
    bold: true
  }
}
path_yes: "YES  (used ≤ 56)" {
  style: {
    font-color: "#166534"
    bold: true
  }
}
path_no: "NO  (used > 56)" {
  style: {
    font-color: "#991B1B"
    bold: true
  }
}
single_block: "ONE BLOCK PATH" {
  style: {
    fill: "#D1FAE5"
    font-color: "#064E3B"
    border-radius: 8
    bold: true
    stroke: "#059669"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
  step_a: |'md
    **STEP 3a: Zero-fill**
    `memset(data + used, 0, 56 − used)`
    Fill bytes `[used .. 55]` with `0x00`
    Zero-fill count = `56 − used` bytes
    _(may be 0 bytes if used = 56, i.e. len = 55)_
  '| {
    style: {
      fill: "#A7F3D0"
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  step_b: |'md
    **STEP 4a: Write length field**
    `data[56..63]` = 64-bit big-endian `len × 8`
    Eight bytes, MSB first:
    `data[56] = bit_len >> 56`  ···  `data[63] = bit_len & 0xFF`
  '| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FDE68A"
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  result_a: |'md
    **RESULT: 1 BLOCK**
    `total_padded = 64`
    `num_blocks = 1`
    Block 0: `data[0..63]`
    ─────────────────────────
    `[msg][0x80][zeros][len×8]`
  '| {
    style: {
      fill: "#059669"
      font-color: "#FFFFFF"
      border-radius: 8
      bold: true
    }
  }
  step_a -> step_b -> result_a
}
two_block: "TWO BLOCK PATH" {
  style: {
    fill: "#FEE2E2"
    font-color: "#450A0A"
    border-radius: 8
    bold: true
    stroke: "#DC2626"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
  step_c: |'md
    **STEP 3b: Zero-fill remainder of Block 0**
    `memset(data + used, 0, 64 − used)`
    Fill bytes `[used .. 63]` with `0x00`
    Zero-fill count = `64 − used` bytes
    _(Block 0 is now complete but has no length field)_
  '| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FECACA"
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  step_d: |'md
    **STEP 3c: Zero-fill Block 1 bytes 0–55**
    `memset(data + 64, 0, 56)`
    Bytes `[64 .. 119]` = `0x00`
    _(length field goes at end of Block 1)_
  '| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FECACA"
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  step_e: |'md
    **STEP 4b: Write length field in Block 1**
    `data[120..127]` = 64-bit big-endian `len × 8`
    `data[120] = bit_len >> 56`  ···  `data[127] = bit_len & 0xFF`
  '| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FDE68A"
      border-radius: 6
    }
  }
  result_b: |'md
    **RESULT: 2 BLOCKS**
    `total_padded = 128`
    `num_blocks = 2`
    Block 0: `data[0..63]`
    Block 1: `data[64..127]`
    ─────────────────────────────────────────
    `[msg (0..55)][0x80][zeros]` · `[zeros (56 bytes)][len×8]`
  '| {
    style: {
      fill: "#DC2626"
      font-color: "#FFFFFF"
      border-radius: 8
      bold: true
    }
  }
  step_c -> step_d -> step_e -> result_b
}
boundary_annotation: |'md
  **⚠ THE 56-BYTE BOUNDARY TRAP**
  | `len` | `used = len+1` | Condition | Blocks |
  |-------|----------------|-----------|--------|
  | 54    | 55             | 55 ≤ 56 ✓ | **1**  |
  | **55**| **56**         | 56 ≤ 56 ✓ | **1** ← last single-block len |
  | **56**| **57**         | 57 > 56 ✗ | **2** ← first two-block len |
  | 57    | 58             | 58 > 56 ✗ | **2**  |
  | 119   | 120            | 120 > 56 ✗| **2**  |
  | 120   | 121            | 121 > 56 ✗| **3**  |
  One extra input byte (`len=55` → `len=56`) adds an **entire extra 64-byte block**.
  The condition `used > 56` (equivalently `len ≥ 56`) triggers the two-block path.
'| {
  near: bottom-center
  style: {
    fill: "#1E1B4B"
    font-color: "#E0E7FF"
    border-radius: 10
    stroke: "#6366F1"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}
formula_annotation: |'md
  **General Formula (any len)**
  `used        = len + 1`
  `total_padded = ⌈(used + 8) / 64⌉ × 64`
  `           = ((used + 8 + 63) / 64) × 64`  _(integer arithmetic)_
  `num_blocks  = total_padded / 64`
'| {
  near: top-right
  style: {
    fill: "#312E81"
    font-color: "#EEF2FF"
    border-radius: 8
    stroke: "#818CF8"
    stroke-width: 1
  }
}
input -> compute_used -> branch
branch -> path_yes -> single_block
branch -> path_no -> two_block